WEBVTT

00:08:58.269 --> 00:09:00.287
his oncologist said,

00:09:00.287 --> 00:09:03.535
"Tell Terence that better days are just ahead."

00:09:03.535 --> 00:09:05.917
Days before he died.

00:09:05.917 --> 00:09:07.350
Yet Ira Byock,

00:09:07.350 --> 00:09:09.698
the director of palliative medicine at Dartmouth

00:09:09.698 --> 00:09:12.629
said, "You know, the best doctor in the world

00:09:12.629 --> 00:09:17.237
has never succeeded in making anyone immortal."

00:09:17.237 --> 00:09:23.743
So what the experts call "denial," I call "hope,"

00:09:23.743 --> 00:09:26.077
and I'd like to borrow a phrase

00:09:26.077 --> 00:09:29.298
from my friends in software design.

00:09:29.298 --> 00:09:32.860
You just redefine denial and hope,